# Video Asset Tools Configuration
# Copy this file to your video project repository root as .video-tools.env
# DO NOT commit .video-tools.env to git (it contains environment-specific paths)

# ============================================================================
# REQUIRED: SSD Backup Location
# ============================================================================

# Path to your external SSD backup drive
# This is where archived projects are stored
SSD_BASE=/Volumes/T7/youtube-PUBLISHED/appydave

# ============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: AWS Configuration (for future S3/Glacier integration)
# ============================================================================

# AWS credentials (or use AWS_PROFILE to reference ~/.aws/credentials)
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=AKIA...
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=...
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1

# S3 bucket for video archive storage
# S3_BUCKET=appydave-video-archive
# S3_PREFIX=appydave/

# Glacier vault for long-term storage
# GLACIER_VAULT=appydave-long-term-archive

# ============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: Lifecycle Rules (for future automation)
# ============================================================================

# Days to keep projects on SSD before moving to S3
# SSD_RETENTION_DAYS=90

# Days to keep in S3 Standard before transitioning to Glacier
# S3_RETENTION_DAYS=180

# ============================================================================
# Notes
# ============================================================================

# 1. SSD_BASE path format:
#    - Mac: /Volumes/DriveName/path
#    - Windows (Git Bash): /c/path or /d/path
#    - Linux: /mnt/drive/path

# 2. For team environments:
#    - Each developer creates their own .video-tools.env
#    - Different SSD mount points per machine
#    - Same relative structure expected

# 3. Git ignore rules:
#    - .video-tools.env should be in .gitignore
#    - This .env.example IS committed for reference
